Questions 

1. WRITE A QUERY TO DISPLAY TOTAL SALARY NEEDED TO PAY EACH JOB IN EMPLOYEE TABLE.<br>

  SELECT SUM(SAL) ,JOB FROM EMP
  GROUP BY JOB;

  SUM(SAL) JOB
---------- ---------
      4150 CLERK
      5600 SALESMAN
      5000 PRESIDENT
      8275 MANAGER
      6000 ANALYST


2.WRITE A QUERY TO DISPLAY THE DEPARTMENT NUMBER WHICH HAS MORE THAN 2 EMPLOYEES AND<<br> 
THE TOTAL AMOUNT REQUIRED TO  PAY THE MONTHLY SALARIES OF ALL THE EMPLOYEES IN THAT<br>
DEPARTMENT SHOULD BE MORE THAN 9000.<br>

 SELECT DEPTNO,COUNT(*) ,SUM(sal)
 FROM emp
 GROUP BY deptno
 HAVING COUNT(*) > 2 AND SUM(sal) > 9000
   
    DEPTNO   COUNT(*)   SUM(SAL)
  --------- ---------- ----------
       30          6       9400
       20          5      10875


3.WRITE A QUERY TO DISPLAY NUMBER OF EMPLOYEES WORKING IN EACH DEPARTMENT AND ITSâ€™<br> 
AVERAGE SALARY BY EXCLUDING ALL THE EMPLOYEES WHOSE SALARY IS LESS THAN THEIR COMMISSION.<br>

 SELECT COUNT(*),AVG(SAL),DEPTNO
 FROM EMP
 WHERE SAL >COMM
 GROUP BY DEPTNO

    COUNT(*)   AVG(SAL)     DEPTNO
   -------- ---------- ----------
        3       1450         30

4.WRITE A QUERY TO DISPLAY THE SALARIES WHICH HAS REPETITIONS IN THE SAL COLUMN OF EMPLOYEE TABLE.<BR>

 SELECT COUNT(*),SAL FROM EMP
 GROUP BY SAL
 HAVING COUNT(*) >=2

     
  COUNT(*)        SAL
---------- ----------
         2       1250
         2       3000


